contentrichtext.text: {{Italic title prefixed|3}} '''USS ''Chatham''''' is a name used more than once by the [[U.S. Navy]]: * {{USS|Chatham|1836|6}}, an iron side wheel steamer was built in 1836. * {{USS|Chatham|ID-2510}} was launched in 1916 by Maryland Steel Company, Sparrows Point, Maryland. * {{USS|Chatham|CVE-32}}, was transferred to the United Kingdom 11 August 1943 under lend-lease and renamed HMS ''Slinger''. * {{USS|Chatham|AK-169}} was launched 13 May 1944 by Froemming Brothers, Milwaukee, Wisconsin. {{Shipindex}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Chatham}} [[Category:United States Navy ship names]]
